24/11/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Nine Romanians serving in Afghanistan were awarded US Army commendation medals at an official ceremony Sunday (23 November). The awards cited their considerable efforts to ensure security and stability in Afghanistan.
In other news, the US Army gave two semi-armoured Hummer vehicles to Romanian engineering troops in Al Hilah, Iraq last week. Radio Romania Actualitati reports the aim was to provide better protection to those serving with the international coalition forces.
On Monday, meanwhile, Europol director Jurgen Storbeck visits Bucharest, where he is expected to sign a co-operation agreement with the government. (Rompres, ACT Media - 24/11/03)
